armorstatues.item.armor_stand.descriptio: Use %s + %s with an empty hand to open configuration screen.
armorstatues.screen.alignments.block.des: Align an armor stand placed on a surface so that a block held by it appears on the surface.
Align an armor stand in the center of the block position it is placed on.
Align an armor stand at the corner of the block position it is placed on.
Align an armor stand placed on a surface so that a non-tool item held by it appears flat on the surface.
armorstatues.screen.alignments.itemFloat: Align an armor stand placed on a surface so that an item held by it appears upright on the surface.
armorstatues.screen.alignments.tool.desc: Align an armor stand placed on a surface so that a tool held by it appears flat on the surface.
armorstatues.screen.failure: Unable to modify armor stand data: %s
armorstatues.screen.finished: Finished sending queued armor stand data
armorstatues.screen.rotations.pose.head: Head
armorstatues.screen.rotations.tip1: Hold the Shift or Alt key to lock sliders to a single axis!
armorstatues.screen.rotations.tip2: Use the arrow keys to move sliders more precisely! Focus a slider first by clicking.
armorstatues.screen.style.invisible.desc: Makes the statue itself invisible, but still shows all equipped items.
armorstatues.screen.style.name: Set a name to display above the entity if enabled.
armorstatues.screen.style.noBasePlate.de: Hide the stone base plate at the statue's feet.
armorstatues.screen.style.noGravity.desc: Prevents the statue from falling down, so it may float freely.
armorstatues.screen.style.sealed.descrip: The statue can no longer be broken, equipment cannot be changed. Disallows opening this menu in survival mode.
armorstatues.screen.style.showArms.descr: Shows the statue's arms, so it may hold items in both hands.
armorstatues.screen.style.showName.descr: Render the statue's name tag above it's head.
armorstatues.screen.style.small.descript: Makes the statue half it's size like a baby mob.
armorstatues.screen.vanillaTweaksCredit: Some content on this page originates from the Vanilla Tweaks "Armor Statues" data pack. Click this button to go to their website!
